The Akwa Ibom state government said it is collaborating has with the World Bank to execute various micro projects worth N50 million in no fewer than five communities across the state aimed at enhancing the development of its rural dwellers. The projects according to the state government would be executed by the state Community and Social Development Project (CSDP). The Commissioner for Economic Development and Ibom Deep Seaport, Mr Akan Okon made this known at the presentation of cheques to the  community leaders during a Two-Day Training Programme of Community Project Management Committee members and Stakeholders in Uyo. The five benefiting communities include, Nka Unwana Essien Enang in Etinan LGA, Nka Esit kiet in Ini LGA, Renewed Life Vulnerable Group in Etinan, Like minds vulnerable group in Oruk Anam LGA and Mbiafun Ikot Abasi, Ini LGA Okon said that the disbursed fund would help the benefiting communities to execute micro projects that would enhance the well-being of Akwa Ibom people adding that the administration of  Gov Udom Emmanuel aims at transforming rural communities through life touching micro projects. He urged stakeholders of the benefiting communities to ensure that they implement and execute their projects as it would attract more development to their respective communities. “The way you implement this project in your various communities would serve as an encouragement for the state government and World Bank to do more. “I want to employ all of you to make sure that the money released to you for the micro project is used for that purpose,” the commissioner said. Earlier, the General Manager, state agency for Community Development and Social Projects, Mr Ishmael Akpan, said that the training would enable stakeholders of the benefiting communities to have the necessary skills and knowledge to manage the disbursed funds during implementation of the micro projects.